A simple Corellian dessert cake. Eating this dessert makes you light on your feet and able to dodge attacks more easily.
A small pastry eaten by the handful. These things tase like pet food, but at least you feel a little more empathetic towards creatures.
A gooey biscuit served drenched in carbosyrup. This item is fit only for consumption by pets.
Basic alcohol stock made from some kind of cereal resource. This is a component of a beverage and should not be consumed by itself.
A protein enhanced synthetic vegetable.
A tasty fortified steak substitute designed to withstand long space travel. Eating this hearty meal makes you feel like you could shrug off a little more damage than usual.

A vile smelling stew favored by members of the Hutt race. Only those with willpower can stand to eat a full serving of Cho-Nor-Hoola. Ingredients in this dish are also known to be antitoxins and make you more resistant to poisons.
A healthy meal made of soypro cooked in purified animal blood. This foul smelling dish thickens your blood and makes you more resistant to bleeding.
A native Trandoshan dish, this meal is reported to have amazing, albeit short rejuuvenating properties.
Sliced meat served in a seasoned miasra sauce. There is something odd about this dish that makes your skin a little more flame retardant. Maybe that's why it tastes so funny.
A vegetable mush often served as a side dish in cantinas.

A healthy wrapped meal favored by Mon Calamari for its memory enhancing properties. This meal makes you keenly aware of your actions. Your enhanced observations gives you a bonus to experience earned.
A traditional Twi'lek meal. Eating this dish gives you a boost to your attributes.
A spiced toast popular with nobility. Eating this dish increases your fortitude and makes you resistant to diseases.
A meat dish common to cantina menus. Eating this dish gives you a boost to your attributes.
A spicy food commonly found in cafes on Coruscant. Eating this dish gives you a boost to your attributes.
A high quality of Veghash favored by the rich. Eating this nutritious dish makes you feel tough and quick, giving you a small defensive advantage to melee attacks.
A very expensive and sweet dish that features toughened meat in a syrupy sauce. Medics that eat this dish may find that they are able to enhance their patients more effciently.
A dish made from hide strips smothered in oil and milk. A dish usually packed and eaten by scouts and rangers, it is rumoured to make that eat it more stealthy.
An extremely spicey sauce! Be careful! Eating this dish makes your blood boil and your muscles buldge.
Butter made from a Bantha's milk.
A thin pastry bread. This item is fit only for consumption by pets.
A greasy dinner pastry common to the Wookiee diet. Eating this tasty dessert gives a boost to your attributes.
A popular snack food filled with rice and fruit. Eating this dessert heightens your visual accuity, which could be useful when surveying for hidden resources.
A special pre-sweetened cake mix.
A healthy bread-like dessert. Eating this dish will cause you to immediately burst run at a higher efficiency.
Extra sweet cake made with carbosyrup. Eating this dessert increases your attention to detail. giving you and assembly bonus when you craft any sort of item.

A gooey pastry common to Mos Espa. Invented by the culinary genius Professor Umlaut. This dessert, usually prized by scouts and rangers, makes you more accurate and efficient when deploying and throwing traps.
A baked dessert made with flower fruit. This item is fit only for consumption by pets.
A delicious pastry made with light fruits and sweet cake mix. Medics that eat this dessert find that they are able to heal their patients more efficiently.
A rich and thick pie thought to have been invented by Baron Hodor of Teyr. Eating this dessert makes you light on your feet and able to dodge attacks more easily.
A frozen dessert favored by Wookiees. Eating this desert makes you a little more resiliant to the rigorous process of cloning, and will reduce the amount of wounds taken from the procedure.
An unusual mixture of fruits, served creamed. Eating this dessert gives you a boost to your attributes.
Delicious spcied candies. Eating this dessert before you are incapacitated may help you regain consciousness faster.
A sweet pastry often served at formal dinners. Eating this tasty dessert gives you a boost to your attributes.
A sticky, sweet pastry. This item is fit only for consumption by pets.
A sweet pastry with a hallow center. Valued highly by smugglers, eating this dessert helps to counteract the detrimental effects of consuming spice.

A favorite drink of ruffians, due to its terrible flavor and strong aftertaste. You have to be tough to put down a Deuterium-pyro. Drinking this beverage sharpens your sight and steadies your aim, giving you a brief advantage when using a ranged weapon.
A fermented Wookiee beverage. Light by Wookiee standards. Drinking this beverage sharpens your sight and sense of smell, giving you a slight advantage when fighting creatures.

Probably the most common alcoholic beverage in the galaxy. Corellian Ale has a sweet flavor and a medium weight body. Drinking this beverage sharpens your sight and quickness reflexes, giving you a brief advantage when fighting in melee combat.
A protein enhanced milk beverage. Medics that drink this beverage find that they are able to cure their patients of afflictions more efficiently.
Drink Container. A very large drink container designed to hold a crafted beverage. This enhanced container offers a moderate bonus to the amount of beverage created when used in crafting.
A sweet berry wine with light flavors. A great dessert wine. This beverage is chock full of vitamins that assist in the clotting of blood, increasing your resistance to bleeding.
A rare alcoholic beverage that lights up with phosphorescent glow when exposed to oxygen. This beverage contains neutralizing properties that increase your resistance to poisons.
A type of wiskey favored by the Ithorian race. Drinking this beverage makes your skin feel glossy and moist, increasing your resistance to fire.

There is no brandy more flavorful and savory than Corellian Brandy. Must be made with real Corellian fruits...otherwise its just brandy. Ingredients in this beverage are known to be potent antidotes, increasing your resistance to disease.

T'ssolok is an intense Twi'lek liqour that is always served in a decorative decanter. While the standing flavor of T'ssolok is not particularly good, the aftertaste is delicious. Studies have shown that those who drink this beverage are more receptive to enhancements and may experiance increased enhancement duration.
A rare brandy made from the fruit and berries of Talus. Drinking this beverage gives you a boost to your abilities.
A strong alcohol beverage made from fungus and alcohol stock. Drinking this beverage gives you a boost to your attributes.
Another rough wookie beverage made from dried bone and hide mixed with alcohol stock. Drinking this beverage gives you a boost to your attributes.
A sweet form of port native to Bespin. Drinking this beverage expands your mind and opens your eyes to new possibilites. You may find experimentation easier while crafting any sort of item.

This drink is probably the strongest in the galaxy. Highly dangerous. After drinking this beverage, you begin to notice the slightest change in your opponent's aim, making it easier for you to predict their attack.
A vegetable based beer that is as thick as it is green. Drinking this beverage enhances your reflexes and gives you a better chance to block incoming attacks.
A heavy food additive. This can only be used in a Heavy additive slot during food crafting.
Drink Container. A massive, tempurture regulated drink container designed to hold a crafted beverage. This container offers a large bonus to the amount of beverage created when used in crafting.
The Galaxy's most potent fire water: this stuff is as strong as it comes. Drinking this beverage gives you a boost to your attributes.

A strange reactive beverage. It burns the tongue while at the same time freezes the throat. This spicy beverage makes you feel like you could take on the world and shrug off a little more damage than usual.

A curdled dish known for the tangy explosion of flavor experianced when mashed against the roof of the mouth. Medics that eat this dish find that they are able to heal their patients more efficiently.
An unidentifiable dish populated by Dexter Jettster in the years following the battle of Naboo. Eating this dish gives you a boost to your attributes.
A rare pudding treat that crackles and pops when you eat it. Eating this treat makes you light on your feat and able to dodge attacks more easily.

The Firespray-class patrol and attack ship has been recently re-introduced to the market by Kuat Systems Engineering. Although the original design was generated a number of years earlier, the prototype vessels built at the time were all lost in the hangar they were being stored during an unfortunate prison escape incident. A sole ship survived the catastrophe and the design has since attained some notoriety owing to the escapades of the pilot. Rather than building to contract, the KSE has generated the Firespray design as a project to shop around and had fronted all the cash for the prototypes, confident that once people had seen their performance purchase orders would come rolling in. Instead the loss of the prototypes put the company in dire financial straights with nothing concrete to show for the Firespray project, and no way to generate interest for the product through demonstrations. Having already drained accounts originally stocked by a huge financial outlay, KSE mothballed the project and everything that had been built so far, including the reams of technical data and all of the specialized tools to build the prototype vessels. KSE then went on to enhance their existing offerings and go to carve an even larger niche for themselves in the market for post-sale ship upgrade kits.
